<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Floating replaced elements with autop and bottom margins</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#inline-replaced-height" />
        <meta name="flags" content="image" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Verify floating replaced elements with margin-top or margin-bottom set to auto become a used value of '0'." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #d1
            {
                border: 3px solid green;
                background: red;
                height: 83px;
                width: 100px;
            }
            #d2
            {
                clear: both;
                float: left;
                background: blue;
                height: 50px;
                width: 100px;
            }
            img
            {
                float: left;
                margin-top: auto;
                margin-bottom: auto;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the blue box is in the top left corner of the green box and there is no red visible on the page.</p>
        <div id="d1">
            <img alt="Test Image" src="../../../Support/blue100x33.png" />
            <div id="d2"></div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>